This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it focuses on improving neural machine translation models. It also involves the use of deep neural networks, which is a common topic in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper also proposes a new algorithm for dynamic layer aggregation, which involves learning probabilities and making decisions, indicating that it may fall under the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Additionally, the use of capsule networks and computer vision techniques suggests that it may also be relevant to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves experiments and empirical evaluations, which may suggest that it could also be relevant to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
